issue.title: [Bug] Application crashes when we pass Object in the option label for Dropdown component.
issue.body:
### Version Information
3.5.15-cloud-lts 

### Environment
ToolJet Cloud

### What is the expected behaviour?
The dropdown option should be blank and it should show an error in debugger.

### What is the current behaviour?
As we pass Object in the Option Label and click on the dropdown, the app crashes. User is redirected to 'Something went wrong' page.

### How to reproduce the issue?

1. Drag and Drop a dropdown component to the canvas.
2. Edit the Options of Dropdown component.
3. Pass an object value, say {{{a:1}}} in any of the options.

commits.message:
feat: Implement invoicing feature

This commit introduces the initial version of the billing and invoicing feature, allowing users to generate and manage customer invoices.

Key changes:
- Adds a new 'Billing' page at `/billing` to display a list of all generated invoices.
- Integrates a 'Generate Invoice' button on the 'Sales Orders' page, which appears for orders with 'Completed' status.
- Implements the back-end logic to create a new invoice record. A new `invoiceService` handles this functionality, using `fetch` for local mode to align with existing patterns.
- Populates the 'Billing' page with a table of invoices, showing key details like ID, customer, dates, status, and total.
- Creates a detailed invoice view, accessible by clicking on an invoice in the list. The view appears in a dialog and includes a 'Download PDF' button.
- Adds a utility `generateInvoicePDF.js` to create a PDF document for the selected invoice, reusing the existing `jsPDF` library.
- Adds a 'Billing' link to the main navigation sidebar for users with 'Admin' or 'Manager' roles.

Note on linting: The `npm run lint` command reports 11 errors. These are pre-existing issues in other parts of the codebase and are not related to the new billing feature. The single lint error in a modified file (`ApiModeContext.jsx`) was fixed.

issue.title: Use parallel gzip compression via host pigz

labels.name: build/scripts/tools
labels.description: pull request/issues for build, scripts and tools related changes

issue.body:
[pigz](https://www.zlib.net/pigz) is a drop-in/fully functional replacement for `gzip` that exploits multiple processors and multiple cores when compressing data. To enable it, a new option has been introduced under:
```
Target Images > Use pigz for parallel gzip compression
```
which serves as an opt-in to insure that users wanting reproducible builds are not surprised by different checksum values when building on their own (see: https://openwrt.org/docs/guide-developer/security#reproducible_builds). This assume that the build bot farm will be using single-threaded `gzip` and not `pigz` for compression.

Additionally several `.mk` files have been modified to selectively use `pigz` to accomplish compression tasks.

Value proposition of using `pigz` is a speed up appox 10-20x when the build system compresses my standard `openwrt-x86-64-generic-ext4-combined.img` which is 962 MB total size with 192 MB kernel partition + 768 MB rootfs partition with 34% of data/the rest of the partitions being empty space.

Time to compress the image on...
AMD Ryzen 9950X processor (16C/32T)
* using `gzip -9`: approx 20 sec
* using `pigz -9`: approx 1 sec

AMD Ryzen 5 7600 processor (6C/12T)
* using `gzip -9`: approx 24 sec
* using `pigz -9`: approx 2 sec

Another test was running `make` after having already built all the packages which effectively just recreates the images after checking that everything is built. Here the speed up was a modest 37% increase.

On the AMD Ryzen 9950X processor (16C/32T)
* Using `gzip` (no `pigz` on the host system), the total process took 1 m 38 sec
* Using `pigz`, the total process took approx 1 m 2 sec

The PR has been tested both with and without `pigz` on the host system, in both cases the build of `r30780-9736d4214128` (with this PR applied) finished successfully.

Build system: x86/64
Build-tested: x86/64-glibc
Run-tested: x86/64-glibc (Intel N150 based box)


issue.title: request route_maps and route_map_fn features for FastMCPProxy to reduce security risks.

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: Improvement to existing functionality. For issues and smaller PR improvements.

issue.body:
### Enhancement

FastMCPOpenAPI has features to exclude/re-map  back-end server routes by route_maps and route_map_fn.
Those features are lacked in FastMCPProxy, so proxy has to expose all backend server tools (except adding prefix to name).

as the result,  integrating  FastMCPProxy with 3rd party MCP, getting security risks.
since 3rd party MCP server, like playwright-mcp, may provide the abilities to run scripts and upload files, besides useful features.

performed_via_github_app.description:
Codecov provides highly integrated tools to group, merge, archive and compare coverage reports. Whether your team is comparing changes in a pull request or reviewing a single commit, Codecov will improve the code review workflow and quality.

## Code coverage done right.Â®

1. Upload coverage reports from your CI builds.
2. Codecov merges all builds and languages into one beautiful coherent report.
3. Get commit statuses, pull request comments and coverage overlay via our browser extension.

When Codecov merges your uploads it keeps track of the CI provider (inc. build details) and user specified context, e.g. `#unittest` ~ `#smoketest` or `#oldcode` ~ `#newcode`. You can track the `#unittest` coverage independently of other groups. [Learn more here](
http://docs.codecov.io/docs/flags)

Through **Codecov's Browser Extension** reports overlay directly in GitHub UI to assist in code review in [Chrome](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/codecov/gedikamndpbemklijjkncpnolildpbgo) or Firefox (https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/codecov/)

*Highly detailed* **pull request comments** and *customizable* **commit statuses** will improve your team's workflow and code coverage incrementally.

**File backed configuration** all through the `codecov.yml`. 

## FAQ
- Do you **merge multiple uploads** to the same commit? **Yes**
- Do you **support multiple languages** in the same project? **Yes**
- Can you **group coverage reports** by project and/or test type? **Yes**
- How does **pricing** work? Only paid users can view reports and post statuses/comments.

issue.title: OOM with official MAME DAT

labels.name: bug
labels.description: A confirmed issues that needs fixing

issue.body: ### Paste the command igir report --dat mame0278.xml --input /media/dirceu/66760EC6760E96C9/Games/Roms/mame --merge-roms nonmerged ### Describe the bug When I use Igir with other DATS like No-intro or Redump, it works normally. But when I use it with a MAME DAT (which is larger than the others), I get an error while reading the DAT and the process terminates. I notice a significant RAM consumption. I have 4GB and it consumes up to 3.2GB. ### Expected behavior I expected the process to go to the end and the rom verification to begin. ### Debug logs [igir.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21496747/igir.log) ### DAT(s) used https://github.com/mamedev/mame/releases/download/mame0278/mame0278lx.zip ### igir version 4.1.2 ### Node.js version N/A ### Operating system Linux Debian 12 ### Additional context

SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration
    
-   Quality Gate (added as a GitHub check) acting at two different levels - first, preventing you from merging pull requests that contain issues - and later, helping you to release only clean, safe code
    
-   Sign up for SonarQube free tier and begin scanning your private and public repositories
    

A [GitHub Action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/sonarcloud-scan) is available in the marketplace to make it easy for you (for projects where automatic analysis isn't available). SonarQube Cloud also integrates smoothly with Jenkins, CircleCI, TravisCI, CirrusCI, and many other tools.

A free tier is available that allows you to explore the benefits of SonarQube Cloud using your public and private repositories. We also provide a no-commitment, [14-day trial](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/) of SonarQube Cloud Team for unlimited team members, up to 1.9M LoC, AI CodeFix recommendations, and more. No need to speak with a sales rep or request a license key - get automatic code analysis results on your private projects in minutes! Want to see more examples of SonarCloud in action? You can [explore current Open Source projects in SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/explore/projects?sort=-analysis_date) that are using the [Clean as You Code](https://www.sonarsource.com/solutions/our-unique-approach/) methodology.

What are you waiting for? SonarQube Cloud helps you consistently deliver cleaner, secure software that future developers will appreciate and your users will love. Start writing Clean Code. [Now](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/)!
